  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA65-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu viricci peṟṟup pukaṉṟa tōḻi talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to the confidante who entered after having received a disembodied voice.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA65">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            amuta muṇkanam mayiliya lāṭṭi</l>
<l>            kiṭaṅki ṉaṉṉa viṭṭukkarai kāṉyāṟṟuk</l>
<l>            kalaṅkum pāci nīrilaik kalāva</l>
<l>            voḷiṟuveḷ ḷaruvi yuṇṭuṟai maṭuttup</l>
<l>            puliyoṭu poruta puṇkūr yāṉai </l>
<l>            naṟkōṭu nayanta vaṉpil kāṉavar</l>
<l>            viṟcuḻip paṭṭa nāmap pūca</l>
<l>            lurumiṭaik kaṭiyiṭi karaiyum</l>
<l>            perumalai nāṭaṉai varumeṉ ṟōḷē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>May she eat ambrosia, our woman of peacock nature,</l>
<l rend="indent2">she who said the man from the land of big mountains will come,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the elephant with a number of wounds that had fought with a tiger,</l>
<l rend="indent">after taking drink at the kajal ghat with bright white waterfall,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the leaves are perturbed in the water with lichen</l>
<l rend="indent2">that is stirred by the forest river with a narrow shore</l>
<l rend="indent3">just like a storehouse<note place="foot">The comparison presumably expresses that the shore is loaded with stranded goods brought by the river.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">roars thunderingly in [self-]protection(?) in between the thunder(?)</l>
<l rend="indent2">from the fearful fight that arose when the loveless forest man,</l>
<l rend="indent2">who longed for [its] tusk, drew [his] bow(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vil cuḻi paṭṭa</term>: here again one is tempted to read <term xml:lang="ta">paṭu</term> as an auxiliary (cf. NA 60.6 <term xml:lang="ta">kavar paṭu</term>), but again the impact is not clear. It could work as a passive, if we take the phrase then as a temporal clause that makes use of the perfective form of the <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> in order to mark the temporal sequence of events: "the fearful fight, when the bow was drawn by the forest man".</note>.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
